<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,160,329]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,256,160,185]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">Notes</emphasis>
:—The newly described species resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Averyanov &amp; Vuong" authorityYear="2018" box="[757,992,160,185]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Gastrochilus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="setosus">
<emphasis box="[757,992,160,185]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">Gastrochilus setosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
morphologically, but differs in lax 2–4 flowered inflorescence (vs. inflorescence dense, with 10 or more flowers), glabrous side lobes of epichile (vs. side lobes of epichile with sparse hairs), and saccate to subglobular hypochile placed at right angle to the epichile (vs. hypochile shortly cylindrical at obtuse angle to epichile). Our plant also somewhat similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="T. P. Lin" authorityYear="1987" box="[1179,1249,268,293]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Gastrochilus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hoi">
<emphasis box="[1179,1249,268,293]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">G. hoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hayata" authorityYear="1920" box="[1303,1444,268,293]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Gastrochilus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="matsudae">
<emphasis box="[1303,1444,268,293]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">G. matsudae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be easily recognized by the morphological characters presented in 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[970,1065,304,329]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">
<tableCitation box="[970,1057,304,329]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="3.[136,224,377,400]" captionText="TABLE 1. The comparison of morphological features of Gastrochilus dresslerii, G. setosus, G. hoi and G. matsudae." pageId="3" pageNumber="148">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
